        <div class="grid-3">
          <article class="content-card">
            <div class="card-tag">Cathy Caruth</div>
            <h3>Unclaimed Experience</h3>
            <p>
              Trauma returns belatedly through flashbacks and repetition. Kaur’s
              poems often narrate what could not be processed at the time of injury.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article class="content-card">
            <div class="card-tag">Judith Herman</div>
            <h3>Safety, Remembrance, Community</h3>
            <p>
              The collection traces a movement from violation to safety, narration,
              and reconnection with others.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article class="content-card">
            <div class="card-tag">Poetic Expression</div>
            <h3>Form as Healing</h3>
            <p>
              Short, visually sparse poems create white space for reflection,
              transforming fragmented experience into shareable story.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
